  <para>
    The &skel; <link
    linkend="RegisteredClass-Refine">refinement</link> process is
    ultimately driven by &sgmts; &#x2014; the refinement <link
    linkend="Enum-RuleSet">rule</link> for each element is determined
    solely by number and configuration of marked &sgmts; in the
    element.  <classname>CheckHeterogeneousEdges</classname> directly
    marks heterogeneous &sgmts; for refinement.  Segment homogeneity
    is defined in <xref linkend="Section-Concepts-Skeleton-Segment"/>.
  </para>

  <para>
    All &sgmts; whose <link
    linkend="Section-Concepts-SegmentHomogeneity">homogeneity</link>
    is less than the given <varname>threshold</varname> will be
    refined, as long as they're in the set described by the
    <varname>choose_from</varname> parameter.
    (<varname>choose_from</varname> is a <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-SegmentChooser"/> object that can
    restrict the scope of the refinement.  Leave it set to <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-FromAllSegments"/> for unrestricted
    operation.)
  </para>

  <para>
    <xref linkend="Figure-hetero_segments"/> shows &sgmts; that have
    been marked for refinement with <varname>threshold</varname>=0.9
    and <varname>choose_from</varname>=<xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-FromAllSegments"/>().  <xref
    linkend="Figure-hetero_segments_refined"/> shows the result of
    refining those segments (with the <link
    linkend="Enum-RuleSet">liberal</link> <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-Bisection"/> rules).

    <figure id="Figure-hetero_segments">
      <title>Heterogeneous Segments</title>
      <mediaobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata format="PNG"
	  fileref="FIGURES/check_mark/hetero_segments.png"/>
	</imageobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata format="EPS"
	  fileref="FIGURES/check_mark/hetero_segments.eps"/>
	</imageobject>
	<caption>
	  <para>
	    Segments with homogeneity less than 0.9 are shown in bold.
	  </para>
	</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <figure id="Figure-hetero_segments_refined">
      <title>Refined Heterogeneous Segments</title>
      <mediaobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata
	    fileref="FIGURES/check_mark/hetero_seg_refined.png"
	    format="PNG"/>
	</imageobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata
	    fileref="FIGURES/check_mark/hetero_seg_refined.eps"
	    format="EPS"/>
	</imageobject>
	<caption>
	  <para>
	    A &skel; refinement based on the bold segments.
	  </para>
	</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
  </para>



